---
// TLDR.astro - Displays the TL;DR section for WestWorld
---
<section id="tldr" class="content-section">
  <div class="section-container">
    <h2 class="section-title">TL;DR</h2>

    <div class="abstract-content">
      <ul>
        <li>
          We propose <strong>WestWorld</strong>, a novel <strong>system-aware MoE architecture</strong> for scaling up the training of trajectory world models across diverse robotic systems.
        </li>
        <li>
          We introduce <strong>knowledge-encoded structural embedding</strong> that provides an explicit inductive bias to enhance <em>zero- and few-shot generalization</em> to unseen robotic systems.
        </li>
        <li>
          We conduct <strong>extensive experiments</strong> to verify the scalability and generalizability of our method, and apply it to a downstream <strong>model-based control task</strong>, demonstrating strong performance in <em>long-horizon planning</em>.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .abstract-content {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 1rem auto 3rem auto;
    background-color: white;
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 2rem 2rem 2rem 2.5rem;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
    line-height: 1.8;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: #333;
    text-align: left;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }

  .abstract-content:hover {
    box-shadow: 0 8px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .abstract-content ul {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }

  .abstract-content li {
    margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
  }

  .abstract-content li:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .abstract-content em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: #555;
  }

  .abstract-content strong {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #2a2f6c;
  }
</style>
